title: FAA issues license for first Starship integrated test flight
summary: The FAA has issued a launch license to SpaceX to the first integrated test flight of the company’s Starship/Super Heavy launch vehicle, scheduled for no earlier than April 17.

title: NASA to Participate in Space Symposium, Discuss Moon to Mars
summary: NASA leadership and other experts will participate in the Space Foundation’s 38th Annual Space Symposium in Colorado Springs, Colorado, and the agency will air two NASA events.

title: SpaceX cleared by FAA to launch first orbital Starship flight
summary: The Federal Aviation Administration issued a Starship launch license to Elon Musk’s SpaceX, a crucial final regulatory step that clears the company to attempt an orbital launch of its towering rocket for the first time.

title: Green light go: SpaceX receives a launch license from the FAA for Starship
summary: "So far they’ve done what they need to do with regard to environmental impact."

title: Orbex CEO resigns
summary: The chief executive of European small launch vehicle developer Orbex stepped down April 14 so that company can go to the “next level” ahead of its first launch.
